rules: Rule1: Provided that Tech Giant acquires Startup, Startup grows Valuation.
Rule2: If Merger is delayed by Review, Merger is challenged by Regulators.
Rule3: Provided that Merger is challenged by Regulators, Merger is approved by Regulators.
Rule4: Either Startup is bankrupt or, if it is not the case that Startup grows Valuation, then Startup does not fold Operations.
Rule5: Under the condition that Startup liquidates Assets, it is not the case that Startup is bankrupt.
Rule6: Either Startup liquidates Assets or Startup is acquired by Competitor.
Rule7: Under the condition that Startup survives Acquisition, if Startup is acquired by Competitor, then Startup is not bankrupt.
Rule8: Provided that Startup pivots Product, Startup survives Acquisition.
Rule9: Startup pivots Product or Startup merges with Partner.
Rule10: If Startup develops AI Platform, then AI Platform is proprietary to Startup.
Rule11: If Startup merges with Partner, then Startup survives Acquisition.
Rule12: Either Tech Giant dominates Market or Startup grows Valuation.
Rule13: Under the condition that Regulators investigate Tech Giant, Tech Giant does not dominate Market.
Rule14: Regulators sanction Tech Giant or, provided that Regulators do not investigate Tech Giant, Regulators do not fine Tech Giant.
Rule15: Either Tech Giant monopolizes Sector or Startup grows Valuation.
Rule16: Provided that Tech Giant appeals Ruling, Court overturns Ruling.
Rule17: Tech Giant appeals Ruling or Tech Giant does not monopolize Sector.
Rule18: If Tech Giant divests Assets, then Tech Giant restructures Business.
Rule19: Provided that AI Platform is patented by Startup, it is not the case that AI Platform is proprietary to Startup.
Rule20: If AI Platform is licensed by Startup, then AI Platform is patented by Startup.
Rule21: Under the condition that Startup settles Lawsuit, if it is not the case that if Startup develops AI Platform then AI Platform is licensed by Startup, then Startup violates Patent Law.
Rule22: Either Startup settles Lawsuit or Startup litigates Lawsuit.
Rule23: Provided that Startup litigates Lawsuit, if it is not the case that if Startup develops AI Platform then AI Platform is licensed by Startup, then Startup violates Patent Law.

Rule24: Under the condition that it is not the case that if Startup negotiates Terms then if it is not the case that Startup grows Valuation then Startup retains Independence, Merger is delayed by Review.

Rule25: Provided that it is not the case that if Startup negotiates Terms then if it is not the case that Startup grows Valuation then Startup retains Independence, Merger is not approved by Regulators.
Rule26: Under the condition that it is not the case that if Startup develops AI Platform then AI Platform is licensed by Startup, Startup does not violate Patent Law.
Rule27: If it is not the case that if Tech Giant complies with Regulations then if Tech Giant appeals Ruling then Court does not overturn Ruling, then Tech Giant divests Assets.

Rule28: Under the condition that it is not the case that if Tech Giant complies with Regulations then if Tech Giant appeals Ruling then Court does not overturn Ruling, it is not the case that Tech Giant restructures Business.
Rule29: Provided that Tech Giant does not acquire Startup, Startup develops AI Platform.
Rule30: If Regulators do not investigate Tech Giant, then Regulators fine Tech Giant.
Rule31: If it is not the case that Startup grows Valuation, then Startup folds Operations.
facts: Fact2: Tech Giant complies with Regulations.
Fact3: Regulators do not sanction Tech Giant.
Fact4: It is not the case that Startup retains Independence.
